The paper deals with the problem of cross-domain face verification using computer vision algorithms, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the optimization of loss functions, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset, which is relevant to graphics (cs.GR).
